//   <div class="ui tiny header">Tiny Header</div>
//   <p>Phasellus ultrices nulla quis nibh. Quisque a lectus. Donec consectetuer ligula vulputate sem tristique cursus. Nam nulla quam, gravida non, commodo a, sodales sit amet, nisi.</p>
// </div>
// 
// Styleguide 2.4.4

// Disabled Headers
//
// A header can show that it is inactive
//
// Markup:
// <div class="ui disabled header">
//   Disabled Header
// </div>
//
// Styleguide 2.4.5

// Attached Headers
//
// A header can be attached to other content
//
// Markup:
// <h4 class="ui top attached header">
//   Sign Up For Our Site
// </h4>
// <div class="ui segment attached">
//   <p>Morbi in sem quis dui placerat ornare. Pellentesque odio nisi, euismod in, pharetra a, ultricies in, diam. Sed arcu. Cras consequat.</p>
//   <p>Praesent dapibus, neque id cursus faucibus, tortor neque egestas augue, eu vulputate magna eros eu erat. Aliquam erat volutpat. Nam dui mi, tincidunt quis, accumsan porttitor, facilisis luctus, metus.</p>
// </div>
// <h4 class="ui bottom attached header">
//   Thanks
// </h4>
//
// Styleguide 2.4.6

// Floating Headers
//
// A header can sit to the left or right of other content
//
// Markup:
// <div class="ui segment">
//   <h3 class="ui right floated header">
//     Go Forward
//   </h3>
//   <h3 class="ui left floated header">
//     Go Back
//   </h3>
// </div>
//
// Styleguide 2.4.7

// Text Aligned Headers
//
// A header can have its text aligned to a side
//
// Markup:
// <div class="ui segment">
//   <h3 class="ui right aligned header">
//     Right
//   </h3>
//   <h3 class="ui left aligned header">
//     Left
//   </h3>
//   <h3 class="ui center aligned header">
//     Center
//   </h3>
// </div>
//
// Styleguide 2.4.8

// Coloured Headings
//
// A header can be formatted with different colors
//
// Markup:
// <h3 class="ui black header">
//   Black
//   <div class="sub header">An excellent color</div>
// </h3>
// <h3 class="ui blue header">
//   Blue
//   <div class="sub header">An excellent color</div>
// </h3>
// <h3 class="ui red header">
//   Red
//   <div class="sub header">An excellent color</div>
// </h3>
// <h3 class="ui green header">
//   Green
//   <div class="sub header">An excellent color</div>
// </h3>
// <h3 class="ui yellow header">
//   Green
//   <div class="sub header">An excellent color</div>
// </h3>
// <h3 class="ui purple header">
//   Purple
//   <div class="sub header">An excellent color</div>
// </h3>
// <h3 class="ui teal header">
//   Teal
//   <div class="sub header">An excellent color</div>
// </h3>
//
// Styleguide 2.4.9

.ui.yellow.header
	color 			$yellow !important

.ui.orange.header
	color 			$orange !important

// Dividing Headers
//
// A header can be formatted to divide itself from the content below it
//
// Markup:
// <h3 class="ui dividing header">
//   The nature of dogs
// </h3>
// <p>Understanding how dogs behave in nature can help us to better fulfill their needs when we bring them into our homes.</p>
// <p>When a puppy enters the world, his first pack leader is his mother. Canine moms teach rules, boundaries, and limitations from day one!</p>
// <p>Newborn puppies don't get a name like we do. The closest thing to a personality is a dog's status within the pack. In the animal world, there are two positions: the leader and the follower.</p>
//
// Styleguide 2.4.10

// Block Headers
//
// A header can be formatted to create a block
//
// Markup:
// <h4 class="ui black block header">
//   Block Header
// </h4>
// <p>Pellentesque habitant morbi tristique senectus et netus et malesuada fames ac turpis egestas. Vestibulum tortor quam, feugiat vitae, ultricies eget, tempor sit amet, ante. Donec eu libero sit amet quam egestas semper. Aenean ultricies mi vitae est. Mauris placerat eleifend leo.</p>
//
// Styleguide 2.4.11

// Inverted Block Headers
//
// A header can have its colors inverted for contrast
//
// Markup:
// <h4 class="ui inverted black block header">
//   Black
// </h4>
// <h4 class="ui inverted blue block header">
//   Blue
// </h4>
// <h4 class="ui inverted red block header">
//   Red
// </h4>
// <h4 class="ui inverted green block header">
//   Green
// </h4>
// <h4 class="ui inverted purple block header">
//   Purple
// </h4>
// <h4 class="ui inverted teal block header">
//   Teal
// </h4>
//
// Styleguide 2.4.12

// Link Headers
// 
// A header can also be a link
//
// Markup:
// <a href="" class="ui link header">
//   This is a Link header
// </a>
//
// Styleguide 2.4.13

.link.header
	color 				$text-colour
	text-decoration 	none
	transition 			$fast-transition

	&:focus,
	&:hover
		color 			lighten(@color, 15%)
		transition		$fast-transition

// Inline headers
// 
// A header can be displayed inline
//
// Markup:
// This is an <div class="ui inline header">inline</div> header
//
// Styleguide 2.4.14

.ui.inline.header
	display 			inline-block